עקּבה    - עקב / ‛âqêb  ‛iqqebâh / aw-kabe', ik-keb-aw'
=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|6117}}; 
=== Noun ===
a heel (as protuberant); hence a track; figuratively the rear (of an army). (lier in wait is by mistake for {{HH|6120}}.): - heel, [horse-] hoof, last, lier in wait [by mistake for {{HH|6120}}], (foot-) step.